column6: This is a simple question about your favorite sport. However, to answer the question about your favorite sport, add one hundred to your age and write the result in digits as an answer. Based on the text above, what is your favorite sport?
column8: You’re planning an upcoming vacation for a whole week and looking for accommodations that fit your preferences. The recommendation system has shortlisted two hotels based on location, price, and amenities that match your criteria.  Your Task:   	 	Read the descriptions of the recommended hotels. 	 	 	Choose which option you prefer. 	   Please imagine these recommendations as if you were genuinely booking a trip. You won't be able to go back after choosing.     Hotel A         Star Rating: ★★★★☆ (4.5)  Price: $105/night  Location: Located in the city center with direct access to main downtown attractions  Amenities:– Free WiFi access is available throughout the property  – All rooms include a TV, a bar and a refrigerator  – The private bathrooms come with a bath and a shower  Brand & Service:– Corporate-owned by a known international hotel brand chain   – Modern décor with contemporary furnishings and an inviting atmosphere  – On-site restaurant and a diverse menu    Hotel B         Star Rating: ★★★★☆ (4.5)  Price: $109/night  Location: Situated in a residential neighborhood, right in the heart of the downtown district  Amenities:– Free WiFi access is available throughout the property  – All rooms include a TV and a fully equipped kitchenette with a refrigerator  – The private bathrooms come with a bath or a shower.  Brand & Service:– Owned & managed by local residents from the region   –  On-site restaurant partnered with local farmers to serve fresh and seasonal ingredients  – Powered in part by renewable energy sources (solar panels) used across its operations       Which hotel do you prefer to stay in during your trip:
